-- EXCLUSIVE-ECB to give banks 48 hours to review health checks - sources
-- 
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 02:55PM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, July 9 (Reuters) - The European Central Bank aims to give banks 48 hours to review the results of detailed health checks before making them public in October, putting the euro zone's new super-regulator on a collision course with bankers who say they need more time, two people familiar with the matter told Reuters on Wednesday.

